UP|52|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|First the bidding. Some people play that they do not open a weak 2 with a 4-card major. Also some people play they don't open a weak 2 with a void. Their reasoning is they may miss a better fit if they do and they don't want to preempt partner.|
pg| ***** 19 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|So, since North has both a 4-card major and a void, those people would not open a weak 2. However, I prefer not putting such restrictions on my weak 2s. I think opening 2@D with the north hand is just fine.|
pg| ***** 20 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|Should east overcall 3@C? Not really. I agree with East's pass. His club suit is only 5 cards long and it is not very good. Has only 1 honor and 1 intermediate. It has another downgrade that many players are not aware of.|
pg| ***** 21 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|The worst holding in an opponent's suit is 3 small. You could easily have 3 quick losers if partner is not short. So holding 3 small diamonds is another bad feature of the east hand.|
pg| ***** 22 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|As for the south hand, in general you should avoid bidding with a singleton in the weak 2 opener's suit as responder unless your hand is very strong. South's hand is not bad but it is not "very strong."|
pg| ***** 23 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|However, with the singleton being the @DA and a nice 6-card suit, I think 2@S is warranted. If north happens to have 3 spades or even honor doubleton 4@S might have plays. But I would not fault south for passing. 2@S is forcing. Asking to be raised with 3-card support or Ax or Kx.|
pg| ***** 24 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|A few play that 2@S is not forcing. That is what Marty Bergen recommends and what I prefer. But most play that 2@S is forcing. And even if not forcing, the weak 2 bidder is not obliged to pass.|
pg| ***** 25 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|Without any question, 2@S bid in this auction as forcing is standard. If you play it as not forcing, it should be alerted unless the alert rules have changed recently. I think, although the ACBL keeps changing the alert rules.|
pg| ***** 26 ***** |


NT|^z@3^b@2^^|cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717:   ^*N|cp||at|As to the play, the @HA was a good lead. But the best shift is probably a club. Then north ends up taking 6 diamonds and 2 clubs because of the 2 finesses and 2 hearts.|
